    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n## Problem\n\nIf `vim.pack.update()` succeeds to do `git checkout ${rev}` but fails to write the lockfile, the state between the lockfile and actual repositories desyncs. And doing `vim.pack.update()` afterwards reports \"Same\" and \"nothing to update\". The lock file won't be updated.\n\nThis desync is less noticable.\n\n## Workaround\n\nRemove lockfile and try to update again?\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```bash\ncd $(mktemp -d)\nmkdir config data\nexport XDG_CONFIG_HOME=$(pwd)/config\nexport XDG_DATA_HOME=$(pwd)/data\nnvim --clean\n:lua vim.pack.add({{src=\"https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig\",version=vim.version.range '2.6.0'}})\n:qa\n# mocking fail write\ncd ./data/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/nvim-lspconfig/\n# 2.7.0\ngit checkout 0203a9608d63eda57679b01e69f33a7b4c34b0d1\ncd -\nnvim --clean ./config/nvim/nvim-pack-lock.json\n# modify version field from \"2.6.0 - 2.6.0\" -> \">=0.0.0\"\n:w\n:qa\nnvim --clean\n:lua vim.pack.update()\n```\n\n`vim.pack.update()`  confirmation buffer shows up. But It reports \"Same\".\nIt leaves lockfile unchanged.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe lockfile upated.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-133+g6d43869aa0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim does not have vim.pack API\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n6.6.87.2-microsoft-standard-WSL2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nweztern\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBuilt from source",
